        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "add doctor coverage for stale gateway locks",
        "body": "AI-assisted: Codex\n\nFixes #49036.\n\n## Summary\nThis change teaches `openclaw doctor` to inspect the gateway lock file, report stale lock ownership, and repair stale gateway locks with `--fix`.\n\n## Root Cause\nThe CLI already had doctor coverage for stale session locks, but the gateway lock had no matching doctor entry point even though the lock subsystem already encoded enough state to detect dead owners and stale files. When the gateway lock became stale, operators had no built-in visibility or guided repair path.\n\n## Fix\nThe gateway lock module now exposes a small inspection helper that reports pid liveness, age, stale reasons, and optional stale-file removal. `doctor` calls a new `noteGatewayLockHealth` helper so stale gateway locks appear in normal doctor output and are automatically removed when the operator runs `openclaw doctor --fix`.\n\n## Validation\n- `pnpm exec vitest run \"src/commands/doctor-gateway-locks.test.ts\" \"src/commands/doctor-session-locks.test.ts\" \"src/infra/gateway-lock.test.ts\"`\n",
